Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya and his Vihiga counterpart Moses Akaranga have hailed devolution for taking services closer to the people.They said Kenyans have realised huge gains, particularly in agriculture sector, since inception of devolution.Speaking at Lusui where Akaranga handed over devolution torch to Oparanya, the duo asked the Treasury to increase allocation to counties to guarantee effective functioning of the devolved units. Oparanya welcomed merging of counties into economic blocs, saying some are too small. -John Shilitsa